 Rivers (Essex), Stanford Bishop and Stanford Regis (Herefordshire), Stanford on Avon (Northamptonshire), Stanford on Soar (Nottinghamshire), and Stanford on Teme (Worcestershire); also from Stamford (Lincolnshire, Northumberland), Stamford Bridge (East Yorkshire), and Standford in Headley (Hampshire), all of which appear as <i>Stanford</i> in medieval documents. The placenames all derive from Old English <i>stān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. This surname has been established in Ireland since the 16th century, where it is also found under the variant <i>Stankard</i>.","History: An early bearer of this surname in North America, Thomas Stanford of England, settled in Charlestown, MA, in the mid 17th century and started a family line that includes Leland Stanford (1824–93), the railroad developer who was governor of CA, a US senator, and the founding benefactor of Stanford University."],"variants":[{"name":"Stanforth","meanings":["English:","mainly a variant of   Stanford  , which may have migrated to North Yorkshire and Northumberland from Norfolk and Suffolk by the North Sea coastal trade.","variant of   Staniforth  ."]},{"name":"Standford","meanings":["English: variant, with intrusive -d-, of   Stanford  . Compare   Standiford  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":7,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705197,"age":80,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"John Stanford was born in 1375, in England. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"1375–":"1375–Surnud","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1382","1405":"1405","England":"England"},"fi":{"1375–":"1375–Kuollut","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1382","1405":"1405","England":"England"},"fr":{"1375–":"1375–Décédé","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–Décédé","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1382","1405":"1405","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"John Stanford est né en 1375, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1375–":"1375–Verstorben","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–Verstorben","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1382","1405":"1405","England":"England","lifeSummary":"John Stanford wurde 1375 in England geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1375–":"1375–Desede","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–Desede","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1382","1405":"1405","England":"England"},"hu":{"1375–":"1375–elhunyt","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–elhunyt","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1382","1405":"1405","England":"England"},"id":{"1375–":"1375–Telah Meninggal","1405–1461":"1405–1461","1375–Male":"1375–Telah Meninggal","1455":"1455","1375":"1375","1461":"1461","1382":"1